g.text: Bed: The sheets feel at once coarse and clammy against your skin. The bed sags beneath your weight as you stretch out and finally close your eyes...
Bed: The window is fixed, the sheets are new, it's easier to fall asleep than ever before...
Bed: The bed is cold and not particularly inviting, but it's yours. The sheets look awful...
Bed: Across the room, the heating system hums its soft lullaby. The mattress feels soft and sheets warm. It only takes you moments for the world to fall away...
The place feels almost like home now, quiet and dignified around you -- a new life by the seaside. You're incredibly tired. The darkness and warmth come fast. You're falling asleep...
The bed underneath you is soft, if lumpy. Waves wash the sand underneath the hut, then grow distant to your ear. In the quiet hum of the organic heater, you fall asleep...
Bed: And then sleep doesn't come.
Bed: The bed is comforting, if a bit run down. Still, you've earned a rest.
The bed is alright. You could sleep here -- later, once night has come. To the sound of waves crashing outside... you've earned it.
Bed: The passage of time has not made the sheets any less coarse. The bed sags beneath your weight as you close your eyes and drift off into an uneasy sleep...

The unchanged linens are only getting greasier and greasier every time you crawl among them. Like some wounded animal you close your eyes and ask for sleep. Just some hours of regular sleep, please...

The room behind your closed eyelids is familiar now. The only home you've ever known. Its darkness gathers. The last thing you hear is the wind blowing in through the broken window, then something comes: a kind of sleep...
It's not easy, but your bones are *so* tired from what feel like *weeks* of work on the case. You have to try. After what feels like hours, you feel you *might* be sleeping...
The bed is still cold from the wind blowing in from the broken window. The mattress creaks as you close your eyes and try your hardest to fall asleep...
Tutorial Agent: The option to go to sleep becomes available every night after 21.00.
Bed: The bed's a little nicer now. You could get a good night's sleep here.
Bed: The sheets feel at once coarse and clammy against your skin. The bed sags beneath your weight as you stretch out and finally close your eyes...
You: No time to rest yet. [Leave.]
Bed: The day has not made the sheets any less coarse. The bed sags beneath your weight as you close your eyes and fall into uneasy sleep...
Bed: Across the room, the heating system hums a soft lullaby. The mattress feels soft and sheets warm. After some time you fall into uneasy sleep...
Bed: The bed is still cold from the broken window, and not too inviting. But it's yours. You've earned it.
